<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">School of Medicine (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 237</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Cultural Artifacts and Social Identity</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">22.08.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">This course introduces students the various aspects of evaluating cultural artifacts. The course begins with the theoretical background of culture and its relevant vocabulary. The following path covers an array of topics including, but not limited to, economy, political appearance of culture, media, heritage, and myth. The focus on these topics will be accompanied by structural issues such as inequality, social class, and cultural capital.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429064&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">School of Medicine (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 238</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Reading and Walking Istanbul</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">22.08.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The objective of this course is to examine the transformation of the City of Istanbul starting from the Turkish Modernity and trace the urban and social developments during the Istanbul’s gaining a global facet. The course will cover different phases and appearances of the urban history and structure of Istanbul. Right to the City, The Understanding of Locality, Urban Gender Relations, Migration, Development of Infrastructure, Formal and Informal Labor Practices, Public Space and Public Health will be part of the readings and discussions.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429065&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">School of Medicine (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 239</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Biopolitics and Health</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">22.08.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">This course deals with Michel Foucault’s theory of biopolitics and its application to ethical debates in the field of health and medicine. Foucault uses the term biopolitics to describe mechanisms that discipline bodies and regulate populations; these include policies that control birth and mortality as well as systems of surveillance that monitor rates of health and disease. Biopolitics is a powerful lens for examining how modern societies shape and define life itself. With a focus on questions of health policies, this course will explore how a biopolitical lens reframes bioethical debates about the nature and value of individual autonomy. Key questions include: What is biopolitics? What are some historical and contemporary mechanisms that control health policies globally and in Türkiye? How do these mechanisms reflect and produce health disparities across axes of race, class, and gender? For this purpose, the government policies on various health issues will be discussed in the light of above mentioned biopolitical perspective.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429231&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
