<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429335&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">School of Medicine (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MED 323</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Health and Society-II</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">12</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">define key terms and priority setting that will be needed in health economics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429335&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">School of Medicine (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MED 323</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Health and Society-II</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">13</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">explain different types of economic evaluation: cost minimization analysis, cost utility analysis, cost consequences analysis and cost benefit analysis</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429335&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">School of Medicine (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MED 323</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Health and Society-II</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">14</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">List the tools of health economics and how they influence priorities</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429335&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">School of Medicine (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">EMED 310</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=449516&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">School of Medicine (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MED 4001</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Electives for Surgical Sciences</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">General Surgery • To be familiar with the anatomy of surgical areas • Explain the symptoms and physical findings of patients with surgical disease, • Analyze the signs and symptoms in a patient. • To summarize the principles of managing surgical patients (acute abdomen, hemodynamic instability, hemorrhages, etc.)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429324&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">School of Medicine (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MED 4001</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Electives for Surgical Sciences</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Thoracic Surgery • Learns the basic principles of chest tube insertion • Management of thoracic trauma patients. • Distinguish the main thoracic surgical pathologies and know their treatments. • Describes the radiological findings of major thoracic surgical pathologies.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429324&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">School of Medicine (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MED 4001</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Electives for Surgical Sciences</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Anesthesiology and Reanimation • Defines the management and stages of general anesthesia as a basis, and lists general anesthesia, • Defines regional anesthesia management, • Describes local anesthesia mechanisms and lists local anesthetics, • Lists basic and advanced monitoring techniques used in anesthesia and intensive care. Analysis of arterial blood gases and acid-base status</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429324&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">School of Medicine (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MED 4001</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Electives for Surgical Sciences</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Plastic, Reconstructive and Aesthetic Surgery • Describes the basic approach to burns and frostbite injuries. • Learns the principles of wound healing. • Defines the approach to the evaluation of craniofacial disorders, cleft lip and palate. • Learns basic breast reconstruction methods • Learns the basic approach for hand and lower extremity injuries • Learns the basic approach to maxillofacial traumas • Learning the treatment of malignant melanoma and non-melanoma skin tumors</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429324&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">School of Medicine (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MED 401</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Internal Medicine</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">To address the symptoms of respiratory disease commonly encountered by the pulmonologist (cough, dyspnea, hemophtys, cyanosis)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429325&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">School of Medicine (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MED 401</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Internal Medicine</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">To review the physiology, pathophysiology, differential diagnosis, pathogenesis, diagnosis and treatment of pulmonary edema, hypoxia, polycytemia.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429325&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
